Crummy way to build distro packages using Docker

$ ./build_package centos7

You might want to update base images first:

$ for image in $(docker images --format "{{.Repository}}:{{.Tag}}") ; do docker pull $image ; done

Or build all images in parallel:

$ parallel ./build_package -- centos7 debian_stretch debian_stretch_rpi3 ubuntu_1604 ubuntu_1804

NOTES:

* The Debian Stretch package works on Buster with no issues
